        <header class="mb-12">
            <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-6xl font-black text-gray-900 mb-8 tracking-tighter leading-tight">
                How to File Your <span class="text-brand-blue">Confirmation Statement in 2026</span>
            </h1>
            <div class="flex items-center space-x-6 p-6 bg-gray-50 rounded-[2rem]">
                <div class="w-10 h-10 rounded-full border-2 border-white bg-brand-blue flex items-center justify-center text-white text-[10px] font-black">RM</div>
                <div>
                    <p class="text-gray-900 font-bold text-sm">Rachel Moore</p>
                    <p class="text-gray-400 text-xs font-medium uppercase tracking-widest">Compliance Lead • March 2026 • 6 min read</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </header>

        <div class="prose prose-blue max-w-none text-gray-600 font-medium space-y-6">
            <p class="text-xl text-gray-900 font-bold leading-relaxed">Every UK company must file a Confirmation Statement at least once every 12 months. Failing to do so can result in your company being struck off. Here's the complete guide.</p>

            <h2 class="text-2xl font-black text-gray-900 mt-10 mb-4">What Is a Confirmation Statement?</h2>
            <p>A Confirmation Statement (CS01) is an annual filing that confirms your company's registered details are correct and up to date. It replaced the old Annual Return in 2016 and covers: registered office address, directors and secretaries, PSC (People with Significant Control) register, share capital and shareholder breakdown, and SIC codes.</p>

            <div class="p-8 bg-blue-50 rounded-[2rem] border-2 border-blue-100 my-8">
                <h4 class="text-brand-blue font-black text-xs uppercase tracking-widest mb-4">Key Deadline</h4>
                <p class="text-blue-900 text-sm font-bold">You have 14 days from your confirmation date to file. Your confirmation date is 12 months after your incorporation date, or 12 months after your last Confirmation Statement.</p>
            </div>

            <h2 class="text-2xl font-black text-gray-900 mt-10 mb-4">Step-by-Step: Filing the CS01</h2>
            <ol class="list-decimal pl-6 space-y-3">
                <li>Log in to your <strong>Companies House WebFiling account</strong> (or use our service).</li>
                <li>Select your company and choose "File a confirmation statement".</li>
                <li>Review all details — registered office, directors, PSC, shares.</li>
                <li>Make any required updates (changes to officers, share structure, etc.).</li>
                <li>Pay the filing fee: <strong>£13 online</strong> (or £40 by post).</li>
                <li>Submit. You'll receive email confirmation from Companies House.</li>
            </ol>

            <h2 class="text-2xl font-black text-gray-900 mt-10 mb-4">2026 PSC Identity Verification Requirement</h2>
            <p>From 2026, PSC details must include verified identity. If your PSC register is out of date or identity verification has not been completed, you must update this during your Confirmation Statement filing. Our Secretarial packages handle this automatically.</p>

            <div class="bg-gray-900 text-white rounded-[2.5rem] p-10 mt-12">
